First basic test with https://www.npmjs.com/package/postcss-dropunusedvars.

```diff
diff --git a/scss/_accordion.scss b/scss/_accordion.scss
index b306540d7..35576ad76 100644
--- a/scss/_accordion.scss
+++ b/scss/_accordion.scss
@@ -3,6 +3,9 @@
 //

 .accordion {
+  --test-component-unused-var: 10px;
+  --test-component-empty-var: ;
+
   // scss-docs-start accordion-css-vars
   --#{$prefix}accordion-color: #{color-contrast($accordion-bg)};
   --#{$prefix}accordion-bg: #{$accordion-bg};
@@ -35,6 +38,7 @@
   align-items: center;
   width: 100%;
   padding: var(--#{$prefix}accordion-btn-padding-y) var(--#{$prefix}accordion-btn-padding-x);
+  font-size: var(--test-component-empty-var);
   @include font-size($font-size-base);
   color: var(--#{$prefix}accordion-btn-color);
   text-align: left; // Reset button style
```

Without the plugin both variables stay in _dist/bootstrap.css_.

Install the plugin with `npm i postcss-dropunusedvars --save-dev` and change our _postcss.config.js_ to:
```diff
diff --git a/build/postcss.config.js b/build/postcss.config.js
index 7f8186d10..5b780fe35 100644
--- a/build/postcss.config.js
+++ b/build/postcss.config.js
@@ -10,6 +10,7 @@ module.exports = context => {
   return {
     map: context.file.dirname.includes('examples') ? false : mapConfig,
     plugins: {
+      "postcss-dropunusedvars": {},
       autoprefixer: {
         cascade: false
       },
```

With the plugin `--test-component-unused-var: 10px;` is removed from _dist/bootstrap.css_ but since `--test-component-empty-var` is in fact used (even if empty), it stays in the file.

Haven't looked at if `postcss-dropunusedvars` can be configured yet ([source code](https://github.com/adobe/spectrum-css/tree/main/tools/postcss-dropunusedvars)), but the basic configuration is not really what we want here.
If it doesn't exist we could write our own `postcss-dropemptyvars` plugin :shrug:

