out of interest, did a quick check to confirm that:

* android + bluetooth mouse: currently shows the dotted underline, but does NOT show a tooltip natively when hovering over an `<abbr>` - even though it does report `any-hover: hover` when a mouse is paired
* iPadOS + bluetooth mouse: shows no dotted underline, and also doesn't show a tooltip

now, i'd be careful/cautious that the android behaviour may be fixed at some point - indeed, i've filed a few mouse-related bugs a while ago about their imperfect mouse implementation. for this reason, i think a naive `hover: none` may be too brutal.

what i would suggest then is, again, the above

```css
abbr[title] {
  cursor: help;
  text-decoration-skip-ink: none;
}

@media (any-hover: none) {
  abbr[title]  {
    text-decoration: none;
  }
}
```

on iOS (which currently doesn't allow pairing a mouse) and iPadOS without a mouse, as well as iPadOS with a mouse, the dotted underline won't show because by default on these platforms there's no underline to begin with.

on android, when no mouse is paired, the underline will be explicitly suppressed. now, the only situation where the underline will show even though it does nothing is android + paired mouse (as in those cases `any-hover: none` will NOT evaluate to true). but, i'd argue, that is then purely an android problem, and it may well be fixed in the future at source. at least with the above, we'll suppress the underline for the most common scenario that currently does show the underline unnecessarily.

