@XhmikosR I just created a workaround (a really bad one...) to avoid the issue for my users, until the issue is resolved.

# Workaround 1

Once the code has been bundled by Webpack, I replace the selector used for the event by a dummy selector, so that the event is never triggered.

https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/blob/fdd306f48100304b09ffd525a4d0cd3f524e0693/js/dist/offcanvas.js#L228

```js
// Workaround to avoid offcanvas hiding when resizing the window.
// See https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/issues/3791 and https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/pull/38125.
fs.readFile(filePath, 'utf8', (error, data) =>
{
	if (error) return console.log(error);
	data = data.replace('[aria-modal][class*=show][class*=offcanvas-]', '[aria-modal][class*=show-dummy][class*=offcanvas-dummy-]');
	fs.writeFile(filePath, data, 'utf8', (error) =>
	{
		if (error) return console.log(error);
	});
});
```

# Workaround 2

Another workaround that works rather well but also has ergonomic issues: the virtual keyboard can be above the input/textarea, so the user cannot see what he is writing.

```js
// See https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/VirtualKeyboard/overlaysContent.
if ('virtualKeyboard' in window.navigator)
{
	window.navigator.virtualKeyboard.overlaysContent = true;
}
```

# Conclusion

So it's not a big deal if this issue is not solved in the short term, but I still hope it will be in the long term. **Because it is really a huge issue: we can NEVER use an input/textarea in an offcanvas with `position: absolute` and with a virtual keyboard (mobile device)**. See https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/pull/38125#issuecomment-1478432972 for further info.

